      %section#code
        .page-header
          %h1
            Apps & Code
            %small web & desktop apps for animation studios, major universities, and more...
        %ul.thumbnails
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail
              %img{:alt => "", :height => "260", :src => "img/production_managment_highlight.jpg", :width => "260"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Production Management Tools
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://reelfx.com", :target => "_blank"} ReelFX Creative Studios
            %em.muted Rails, JS, Backbone, MySQL, Mongo, etc.
            %p Production coordinators want to know that a project is on schedule.  The ReelFX web team and I created numerous internal tools to give them data on a whole project down to individual renders. Select tools that I spearheaded:
            %ul
              %li App for batch review and categorization of pre-viz & concept artwork
              %li Interactive console for managing artist and department quotas
              %li Drag-and-drop interface for assigning shots to artists
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/review_tool.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Animation Review Tools
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://reelfx.com", :target => "_blank"} ReelFX Creative Studios
            %em.muted Flash, Flex, PureMVC, Flash Interactive Server
            %p Animation supervisors want to give animators great feedback. I created web-based tools to allow a supervisor to cue up an animator's work, watch and seek frame-by-frame, draw annotations, and record it all along side his webcam feedback.
            %ul
              %li Additionally, I've created slideshow tools for quickly flipping through, zooming in/out, and commenting on high resolution artwork.
          %li.span3{:style => "clear:left"}
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :height => "260", :src => "img/thesis_highlight.jpg", :width => "260"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 iCanDraw? - M.S. Thesis
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://srlweb.cse.tamu.edu/srlng/people/users/dixon", :target => "_blank"} Sketch Recognition Lab (SRL)
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://tamu.edu", :target => "_blank"} Texas A&M University
            %em.muted Java, SRL Libraries, Wacom
            %p For my Masters of Science in Computer Science, I created a proof-of-concept methodology for a computer to provide direction and feedback for assisting a user in learning to draw a human face as accurately as possible.
            %ul
              %li
                %a{:href => "http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1753459", :target => "_blank"} CHI 2010 Paper
              %li
                %a{:href => "http://uist.acm.org/uist2009/program/#Posters", :target => "_blank"} UIST 2009 Poster
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/infosat_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Online Training for Students
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://itim.tamu.edu", :target => "_blank"} Information Technology Issues Management (ITIM)
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://tamu.edu", :target => "_blank"} Texas A&M University
            %em.muted HTML, CSS, Javascript, Flash, Coldfusion
            %p In 2007-08, I worked on a small team to develop engaging, online, information security training for students at Texas A&M. The state requires each student to complete this training each year and prior years have received much criticism. Our goal was to create entertaining yet informative training, and the user response proved that we were successful.
          %li.span3{:style => "clear:left"}
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:height => "250", :src => "img/campus_map_highlight.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %li.span3
            %h3 Interactive Campus Map
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu/oit", :target => "_blank"} Office of Information Technology
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted Flash, C#.NET, MS SQL, Illustrator
            %p A Flash application I developed in 2004-05 for use by countless Auburn University students, faculty, and visitors. The application remained in service until late 2011.
            %ul
              %li Won the 2005 NACIS Web Mapping Competition
              %li Helped me win the 2006 Auburn University On-Campus Student Employee of the Year
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/au_redesign_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 University Website Redesign
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted HTML, CSS, Dreamweaver, Photoshop
            %p In 2005, I served on a committee to create a conceptual design and then acted as lead developer to turn it into code for mass implementation across the entire Auburn University website. Created templates and documentation for department webmasters to use, as well as helped redesign main pages.
          %li.span3{:style => "clear:left"}
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/eagle_eye_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Streaming Media Website
            %h4 Eagle Eye News
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted PHP, MySQL, Flash, XML
            %p Eagle Eye News is Auburn's student television news station, for which I served as the technical director from 2003-2006. I developed and maintained a site with streaming stories, shows, podcasts, RSS feeds, and viewer statistics.
          %li.span3
            %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://vimeo.com/36626881", :target => "_blank"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/streams_highlight.gif"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Particle Simulation
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://www.viz.tamu.edu/", :target => "_blank"} Visualization Lab
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://tamu.edu", :target => "_blank"} Texas A&M University
            %em.muted C++, OpenGL, GLUT
            %p As an assignment for a Physically-Based Modeling class taken in 2007, I created a flocking simulation to animate particles in a fluid-like motion along targets following a hidden generated spline. The program had a series of parameters to stylize the look, including color.
            %p
              %a.btn{:href => "http://vimeo.com/36626881", :target => "_blank"}
                %i.icon-film
                Watch on Vimeo
