          %li.span3
            %h3 News Intros & Graphics
            %h4 Eagle Eye News
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted Premiere, AE, Photoshop, Blender 3D
            %p Over my three years (2003-2006) as Technical Director for Eagle Eye News, I created two show openers, multiple motion graphics, and countless other fun videos using the entire Adobe Video Production suite.
          %li.span3{:style => "clear:left"}
            %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://vimeo.com/10711846"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/dotd_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Danger of Dangerous Things
            %em.muted Premiere, Canon XL2
            %p As a semester project in 2006, three classmates and I took a short story and adapted it into a short film.  The process included development meetings, storyboards, scripts, location scouting, casting, shooting schedules, recording of voiceovers, post-production, and more.
            %p
              %a.btn{:href => "http://vimeo.com/10711846", :target => "_blank"}
                %i.icon-film
                Watch on Vimeo
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/mascot_video_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Aubie, the Auburn Mascot
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted Premiere, AE, Photoshop, Audition
            %p I created opening sequences and motion graphics for the video submissions of the AU mascot, Aubie, for the 2005 and 2006 UCA National Mascot Competitions. Additionally, I made a few spots for Aubie that made it to the jumbotron at AU football games.
            %ul
              %li The 2005 video won Aubie a first place bid before going to the competition, where he eventually took first place.
              %li The 2006 video won Aubie a third place bid before going to the competition.
          %li.span3{:style => "clear:left"}
            %a.thumbnail{:href => "javascript:popUp('/intro_to_comp')"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/intro_comp_rev_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 Introduction to Computing
            %h4
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu/oit", :target => "_blank"} Office of Information Technology
            %h6
              %a{:href => "http://auburn.edu", :target => "_blank"} Auburn University
            %em.muted Premiere, AE, Maya, Photoshop, Canon XL1
            %p A video and web presentation created in summer 2004 and then revised and reshot in spring 2005 for all new students attending Auburn University's Camp War Eagle (orientation) to learn about all the computing resources available to them and how to get started.
            %p
              %a.btn{:href => "javascript:popUp('/intro_to_comp')"}
                %i.icon-film
                Watch
          %li.span3
            %span.thumbnail{:href => "#"}
              %img{:alt => "", :src => "img/monster_highlight.jpg"}
          %li.span3
            %h3 A Monster Attacks Auburn
            %em.muted Flash, AE, Premiere, Illustrator
            %p A two-minute, hilarious cartoon that I co-created in the spring of 2004 about Auburn University's beloved mascot, Aubie, as a superhero that saves AU from a huge monster.
